OL,3,CMan still suffering flashbacks after
OL,4,Cbeing 'spiked by a friend'
OL,6,FAt first, Harry tried telling himself
OL,7,Fthat nothing had happened to him, and
OL,8,Fhe went a year and a half without
OL,9,Fspeaking about the incident to anyone
OL,10,Felse.
OL,12,FHe said didn't report it to the police
OL,13,Fbecause "saying it out loud" would
OL,14,Fmean accepting what had happened to
OL,15,Fhim.
OL,17,F"I got in the shower and, like a
OL,18,Ftypical repressed man, I said to
OL,19,Fmyself 'no, it didn't happen'.
OL,26,@yD@AOU
