OL,3,CMan still suffering flashbacks after
OL,4,Cbeing 'spiked by a friend'
OL,6,F"The mention of spiking just brought
OL,7,Fit all back up. It just triggered
OL,8,Fsomething in me and I started having a
OL,9,Fpanic attack.
OL,11,F"I started seeing it in my head. Even
OL,12,Fnow, I still feel my mind start to go
OL,13,Fand I feel a little bit uneasy."
OL,15,FBy that time, drinking alcohol had
OL,16,Falso started causing Harry to have
OL,17,Fflashbacks. When his friend Amy asked
OL,18,Fhim why seemed so panicked, and Harry
OL,19,Ffinally told her everything.
